        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In the analyses stratified by lymphoma type, whose results are reported in Table IV, an increased risk among workers exposed to beef meat was mainly apparent for diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (OR = 1.49, 95%CI 0.96–2.33), chronic lymphocytic leukemia/ small lymphocytic lymphoma (OR = 1.35, 95% CI 0.78–2.34), and multiple myeloma (OR = 1.40, 95%CI 0.67–2.94). Stronger increases in risk were observed for each of these 3 subtypes after 16 years or more of exposure (OR 2.00, 95% CI 0.87–4.61; OR",
